title: Woodblock, "Presbyterian Church, Alexandria, Virginia", ca. 1870
medium: wood, with traces of black and white chalk, inking on surface
inscribed:
stamped on verso: "R.F.Cole and Co., Williams, N.Y. 195".
- verso bears writing: "the Presbyterian Church for alexandria - ...Washington a ...?...".
description: vertical rectangle - small square church building, surmounted by a cupola, is seen set among trees, behind a low wall and facing a street, on which are numerous figures.

tombstone.epitaph: Woodblock, "Presbyterian Church, Alexandria, Virginia", ca. 1870. wood, with traces of black and white chalk, inking on surface. Gift of Anonymous Donor. a-d-327.
